As of the 2020 census, there were 56 people, 35 households, and 38 families residing in the village. The racial makeup of the village was 92.9% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]]. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.79% of the population.<ref>{{cite web |title=Junction, Illinois, USA 2020 Census |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Junction_village,_Illinois?g=160XX00US1738778}}</ref>

There were 35 households, out of which 10.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 68.6% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 22.9% had a female householder with no husband present.

The median income for a household in the village was $32,375, and the median income for a family was $42,500. 45.5% of those over 64 were living below the poverty line.

